ry\n!scope=\"col\"|Date\n!scope=\"col\"|Format\n!Version\n!scope=\"col\"|Label\n!scope=\"col\"|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Various\n|31 October 2019\n|{{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" |Original\n| rowspan=\"12\" |[[Warner Records|Warner]]\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"Apple Music\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/dont-start-now-single/1484636581|title=Don't Start Now - Single by Dua Lipa|work=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=31 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia\n| rowspan=\"3\" |1 November 2019\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Contemporary hit radio]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themusicnetwork.com/charts/issues/1261/1261-singles-to-radio/|title=Singles To Radio|website=The Music Network|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://radiodate.it/radio-date/dua-lipa-don-t-start-now-189905-01-11-2019-radiodate/|title=DUA LIPA \"Don't Start Now\" {{!}} (Radio Date: 01/11/2019)|website=radiodate.it|language=en|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |United Kingdom\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/3tqPdBWF9yMbTrfjWvfKV8t/radio-1-playlist|title=BBC - Radio 1 Playlist|website=[[BBC]]|accessdate=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| 5 November 2019\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|website=All Access Music Group|accessdate=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"7\"| Various\n|26 November 2019\n| rowspan=\"7\" |{{hlist|Digital download|streaming}}\n|Dom Dolla Remix\n|<ref name=\"dom dolla\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |6 December 2019\n|Purple Disco Machine Remix\n|<ref name=\"purple disco machine\" />\n|-\n|Zach Witness Remix (Malibu Mermaids Version)\n|<ref name=\"zach witness\" />\n|-\n|18 December 2019\n|Kungs Remix\n|<ref name=\"kungs\" />\n|-\n|10 January 2020\n|Remix EP\n|<ref name=\"remixes\" />\n|-\n|24 January 2020\n|Regard Remix\n|<ref name=\"regard\" />\n|-\n|21 February 2020\n|Live in LA Remix\n|<ref name=\"live\" />\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of UK top-ten singles in 2019]]\n* [[List of Billboard Hot 100 top-ten singles in 2020|List of ''Billboard'' Hot 100 top-ten singles in 2020]]\n* [[List of Billboard Mainstream Top 40 number-one songs of 2020|List of ''Billboard'' Mainstream Top 40 number-one songs of 2020]]\n* [[List of Mainstream Top 40 top 10 singles in 2019]]\n* [[List of number-one singles of 2019 (Ireland)]]\n* [[List of top 10 singles in 2019 (Australia)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Dua Lipa}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance/Mix Show Airplay number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs) number-one singles]]\n[[Category:British disco songs]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Disco songs]]\n[[Category:Dua Lipa songs]]\n[[Category:Nu-disco songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Israel]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Caroline Ailin]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Dua Lipa]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Emily Warren (songwriter)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)]]\n[[Category:Warner Records singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the BoA single|Don't Start Now (BoA song)}}\n{{short description|2019 single by Dua Lipa}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox single\n| name         = Don't Start Now\n| type         = single\n| artist       = [[Dua Lipa]]\n| album        = [[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|Future Nostalgia]]\n| cover        = Dua Lipa - Don't Start Now.png\n| alt          =\n| released     = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|11|1}}\n| format       =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded     =\n| genre        = [[Nu-disco]]<!-- Sourced in the \"Composition\" section. As per [[Template:Infobox song]]: \"This field should include the music genre(s) that best describes the song-->\n| length       = 3:03\n| label        = [[Warner Records|Warner]]\n| writer       = {{hlist|Dua Lipa|[[Caroline Ailin]]|[[Emily Warren]]|[[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]]}}\n| producer     = Ian Kirkpatrick\n| prev_title   = [[Swan Song (song)|Swan Song]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| year         = 2019\n| next_title   = [[Physical (Dua Lipa song)|Physical]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc         = {{External music video|{{YouTube|oygrmJFKYZY|\"Don't Start Now\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Don't Start Now'''\" is a song by English singer [[Dua Lipa]] from her second studio album, ''[[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|Future Nostalgia]]'' (2020). It was released by [[Warner Records]] as the album's [[lead single]] on 1 November 2019. Lipa wrote the song with [[Caroline Ailin]], [[Emily Warren]], and its producer [[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]]. Inspired by music by the [[Bee Gees]] and [[Daft Punk]], \"Don't Start Now\" is a [[nu-disco]] song with several [[1980s in music|1980s]] and [[disco]] elements. It is built around a percolating [[Funk music|funk]] [[bassline]] and [[Accent (music)|accented]] disco strings. In the lyrics, Lipa addresses a former lover about moving on from their breakup. \n\n\"Don't Start Now\" received acclaim from [[Music journalism|music critics]] upon release, with many noting a significant growth in Lipa's sound and identity as a singer. The song was a commercial success worldwide, charting in the top 10 in 40 different countries. It peaked at number two on both the [[UK Singles Chart]] and US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], surpassing 2017's \"[[New Rules]]\" to become Lipa's highest-charting single in the US.\n\nThe music video for \"Don't Start Now\" was directed by [[Nabil Elderkin]], and shows Lipa passing through a basement nightclub and masked ball. To promote the single, the singer performed it on many television programmes, and at several awards shows including the [[2019 MTV Europe Music Awards]] and [[American Music Awards of 2019|2019 American Music Awards]].\n\n==Background==\nLipa wrote \"Don't Start Now\" with the same team who wrote her 2017 single \"[[New Rules]]\" ([[Caroline Ailin]], [[Emily Warren]] and [[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]]). She said working with them again naturally made her choose it as ''[[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|Future Nostalgia]]''{{'}}s [[lead single]] to \"close one chapter of my life and start another\" with a \"new sound\".<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-shares-snippet-of-new-track-dont-start-now-album-2559838|title=Dua Lipa shares new disco-tinged single 'Don't Start Now'|last=Skinner|first=Tom|website=[[NME]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> The song's writing process began at Warren's home in [[Wyoming]] where she and Kirkpatrick were attempting to write a second hit for Lipa following their success with \"New Rules\". During a session with Lipa and Ailin, they all contributed to lyrics that reflected the singer's \"sophisticated, confident, sassiness\".<ref name=\"SU\">{{cite web|url=https://www.songwriteruniverse.com/ian-kirkpatrick-songwriter-2020.htm|title=Ian Kirkpatrick Interview - Hit Songwriter and Producer|last=Kawashima|first=Dale|website=Songwriter Universe|date=20 February 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAlthough the [[bassline]] in the song sounds live, Kirkpatrick created it with [[MIDI]]. It was influenced by similar basslines by the [[Bee Gees]] and [[Daft Punk]] that he listened to growing up. Kirkpatrick described the production as a combination of his favourite [[disco]] and \"Euro-funk\" music, and cited music by [[Two Door Cinema Club]] as an influence.<ref name=\"SU\"/>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Don't Start Now\" has been widely described by music critics as a [[nu-disco]] song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/rs-charts-young-thug-hot-songs-910833/|title=RS Charts: Young Thug's 'Hot' Hits Number One|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=11 November 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Slant\">{{cite web|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review-dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-is-a-euphoric-escape-hatch-to-pops-past/|title=Review: Dua Lipa's Future Nostalgia Is a Euphoric Escape Hatch to Pop's Past|last=Cinquemani|first=Sal|website=[[Slant Magazine]]|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Crack\">{{cite web|url=https://crackmagazine.net/article/album-reviews/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia/|title=Dua Lipa \u2013 'Future Nostalgia' review|last=Cragg|first=Michael|website=[[Crack Magazine]]|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/112303-dua-lipas-new-single-dont-start-now-is-about-moving-on/|title=Dua Lipa's new single Don't Start Now is about 'moving on'|website=[[The List (magazine)|The List]]|date=24 October 2019|accessdate=6 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"musicOMH\">{{cite web|url=https://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia|title=Dua Lipa \u2013 Future Nostalgia|last=Smith|first=Nick|website=[[musicOMH]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> It has numerous [[1980s in music|1980s]] and [[disco]] tropes, and elements of [[Eurodance]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/apr/05/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-review|title=Dua Lipa: Future Nostalgia review \u2013 a dazzling dance through the decades|last=Empire|first=Kitty|author-link=Kitty Empire|website=[[The Observer]]|date=5 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/business/chart-beat/8550118/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-five-burning-questions|title=Five Burning Questions: Billboard Staffers Discuss Dua Lipa's 'Don't Start Now' Hitting the Top 10|author=Billboard Staff|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=4 February 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/dua-lipas-new-album-future-nostalgia-is-an-apocalypse-game-changer-and-the-best-album-of-2020-so-far|title=Dua Lipa's 'Future Nostalgia' Is an Apocalypse Game-changer\u2014and the Best Album of 2020 So Far|last=Fallon|first=Kevin|website=[[The Daily Beast]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> The song is composed in [[Time signature|{{music|time|4|4}} time]] and the [[Key (music)|key]] of [[B minor]], with a [[tempo]] of 124 beats per minute. Constructed in [[verse-chorus form]], the verses have an Em\u2013Bm\u2013G\u2013D\u2013A [[chord progression]], while the chorus follows a Bm\u2013D\u2013Em7\u2013F{{music|sharp}}m7\u2013Gmaj7 sequence.<ref name=\"MN\">{{cite web|url=https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0203029|title=Dua Lipa 'Don't Start Now' Sheet Music in B minor|publisher=Musicnotes.com|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> The track makes use of a percolating [[Funk music|funk]] bassline which interchanges with the beat.<ref name=\"SOS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.soundonsound.com/people/mix-review-march-2020|title=The Mix Review: March 2020|last=Senior|first=Mike|website=[[Sound on Sound]]|date=10 March 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/music-reviews/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-review/|title=Dua Lipa offers up high-octane pop bliss on Future Nostalgia|last=Johnston|first=Maura|author-link=Maura Johnston|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=26 March 2020|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> \"Don't Start Now\" also uses a syncopated Latin [[Woodblock (instrument)|woodblock]], [[laser weapon]] sound effects and clapping samples.<ref name=\"SOS\"/><ref name=\"The Line of Best Fit\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-album-review|title=Dua Lipa - Future Nostalgia|last=Taylor|first=Chris|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/vb5na4/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-listen-review|title=Dua Lipa's Disco Era 'Don't Start Now' Single Review|last1=Mokoena|first1=Tshepo|last2=Jones|first2=Daisy|last3=O'Neill|first3=Lauren|website=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe song opens with a three-chord piano intro from the first part of the chorus with Lipa singing the line, \"If you don't wanna see me\", and ending with a [[Phonographic record|vinyl]] hiss.<ref name=\"MN\"/><ref name=\"TSJ\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thesinglesjukebox.com/?p=28508|title=Dua Lipa \u2013 Don't Start Now|website=[[The Singles Jukebox]]|date=8 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Vox\">{{cite podcast|url=https://podcasts.apple.com/gb/podcast/dua-lipas-disco-fever/id934552872?i=1000462452027|title=Switched on Pop: Dua Lipa's Disco Fever|website=[[Apple Music]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|date=10 February 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> Lipa's vocals eschew modulation and build from a lower [[vocal register|register]] to a natural use of [[melisma]], spanning from [[A (musical note)|A<sub>3</sub>]] to [[D (musical note)|D<sub>5</sub>]].<ref name=\"MN\"/><ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/dua-lipa-dont-start-now/|title='Don't Start Now' by Dua Lipa Review|last=Strauss|first=Matthew|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> The track also builds with the addition of [[Accent (music)|accented]] disco strings,<ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/nov/04/50-great-tracks-for-november-from-dua-lipa-destroyer-selena-gomez-and-more|title=50 great tracks for November from Dua Lipa, Destroyer, Selena Gomez and more|last1=Beaumont-Thomas|first1=Ben|last2=Snapes|first2=Laura|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=4 November 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/article/best-new-music-2019.html|title=Best New Music \u2014 December 6, 2019|author=Vulture Editors|website=[[Vulture.com]]|date=9 December 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> and bursts of disco [[Synthesizer|synths]].<ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/><ref name=\"NME YE\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/features/the-50-best-songs-of-2019-2589036|title=The 50 best songs of 2019|website=NME|date=18 December 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> It has a strong [[Kick drum|kick]] and [[bass drum|bass]] pattern that sparingly uses the [[Bass (sound)|low-end]]. After every fourth [[Bar (music)|measure]], a [[Fill (music)|fill]] is used, such as on the [[Snare drum|snare]]\u2013kick sequence that precedes the second verse.<ref name=\"SOS\"/> A [[rhythm guitar]] loop is added on the second verse, and a crowd noise on the second chorus.<ref name=\"TSJ\"/><ref name=\"Vox\"/> During the final chorus, chordal devices from the [[Breakdown (music)|breakdown]] reappear for [[Texture (music)|texture]] and Lipa sings in [[Call and response (music)|call and response]].<ref name=\"SOS\"/><ref name=\"TSJ\"/>\n\nThe lyrics are similar to Lipa's previous post-breakup song \"New Rules\". However, ''[[Stereogum]]'' notes that while \"New Rules\" dealt with the \"immediate aftermath\" of a breakup, \"Don't Start Now\" is \"a sequel of sorts, proof that those new rules really do work.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2063550/the-5-best-songs-of-the-week-311/franchises/the-5-best-songs-of-the-week/|title=Dua Lipa, HAIM & The Week's Best Songs: Listen|website=[[Stereogum]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> It finds the singer celebrating her independence and using [[Bullet (typography)|bullet point]] instructions to directly address her former lover.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://time.com/5736115/best-songs-2019/|title=The 10 Best Songs of 2019|last1=Chow|first1=Andrew R.|last2=Bruner|first2=Raisa|website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=28 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-new-song-904813/|title=Dua Lipa Returns With Disco Kiss-Off 'Don't Start Now'|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|website=Rolling Stone|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/pop/9345029/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-album-songs-ranking|title=Ranking All 11 Songs on Dua Lipa's 'Future Nostalgia': Critic's Take|last=Gracie|first=Bianca|website=Billboard|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> According to Lipa, the lyrics are about \"moving on and not allowing anyone to get in the way of that.\"<ref name=\"NME\"/>\n==Release==\nIn October 2019, Lipa deleted all her social media posts in preparation for the release of \"Don't Start Now\".<ref name=\"video shoot\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-is-supposedly-releasing-new-single-dont-start-now-in-november|title=Dua Lipa is supposedly releasing new single 'Don't Start Now' in November|last=Kenneally|first=Cerys|website=The Line of Best Fit|date=15 October 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' revealed the single's release date in an article about Lipa's management on 10 October 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/tap-management-expands-hailee-steinfeld-lana-del-rey-1203362923/|title=TaP Management Expands With Hailee Steinfeld Signing, New West Coast Office|last=Herman|first=James Patrick|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=10 October 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20191010225430/https://variety.com/2019/music/news/tap-management-expands-hailee-steinfeld-lana-del-rey-1203362923/|archivedate=10 October 2019}}</ref> Fans of the singer leaked the song's title and lyrics on [[Twitter]] on 14 October 2019, after spotting her filming the music video in [[Brooklyn]].<ref name=\"video shoot\"/> On 22 October 2019, Lipa shared a teaser video on social media featuring a 10-second snippet of the track.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-drops-teaser-for-new-single-dont-start-now|title=Dua Lipa drops teaser for new single 'Don't Start Now'|last=Kenneally|first=Cerys|website=The Line of Best Fit|date=22 October 2019|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'}}s editor Matthew Strauss wrote that the \"French bloghouse\" production suited Lipa and praised the singer for eschewing vocal modulation, saying \"her voice sounds stronger than ever\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/dua-lipa-dont-start-now/|title='Don't Start Now' by Dua Lipa Review|last=Strauss|first=Matthew|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> Brittany Spanos of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' believed the song took Lipa's sound to \"a higher level\" and that she \"finally finds her pop footing,\" regarding it as \"the peak of pop catharsis,\" and among 2019's \"most glamorous new tunes\" and \"strongest bass lines.\"<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-disco-song-you-need-to-know-907761/|title=Song You Need to Know: Dua Lipa, 'Don't Start Now'|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=4 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]''{{'}}s Rachita Vasandani commented, \"It's funky and fun...\u2014what else do we need?\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/11/dua-lipas-latest-track-dont-start-now-is-here-watc.html|title=Dua Lipa's Latest Single and Music Video 'Don't Start Now' Is Here|last=Vasandani|first=Rachita|website=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> \n\nIn his review for ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]'', Robin Murray viewed the track as \"a super-infectious disco burner\", noting \"a [[Chic (band)|Chic]] flavour to the songwriting, given a chrome-plated 2019 overhaul.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/news/dua-lipas-dont-start-now-is-a-super-infectious-disco-burner|title=Dua Lipa's 'Don't Start Now' Is A Super-Infectious Disco Burner|last=Murray|first=Robin|website=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> ''[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]''{{'}}s reviewer deemed it \"an empowerment bop\" and \"funkier number than her former fare, replete with the kind of bass line [[Mark Ronson]] would be proud of.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diymag.com/2019/11/01/dua-lipa-returns-with-empowerment-bop-dont-start-now|title=Dua Lipa returns with empowerment bop 'Don't Start Now'|website=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=9 November 2019}}</ref> [[Jon Caramanica]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'' found the song \"effective but not overambitious\", arguing that Lipa sells its \"kiss-off sentiment with rhythm but not punch.\"<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/01/arts/music/playlist-dua-lipa-ariana-grande-earl-sweatshirt.html|title=The Playlist: Dua Lipa's Disco Blast, and 13 More New Songs|last1=Pareles|first1=Jon|last2=Caramanica|first2=Jon|last3=Russonello|first3=Giovanni|website=[[The New York Times]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Year-end lists ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+\n!Publication\n!Rank\n!Ref.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''\n|{{center|41}}\n|{{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8545893/best-songs-of-2019-top-100|title=The 100 Best Songs of 2019: Staff List|last=Billboard Staff|date=11 December 2019|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]''\n|{{center|1}}\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=The 75 Best Pop Songs Of 2019 |url=https://www.idolator.com/7904444/the-75-best-pop-songs-of-2019?adblock=1&chrome=1 |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=30 December 2019 |accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[NME]]''\n|{{center|17}}\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite web |last=NME |title=The 50 best songs of 2019 |url=https://www.nme.com/features/the-50-best-songs-of-2019-2589036 |website=[[NME]] |date=18 December 2019 |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Stereogum]]''\n|{{center|4}}\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite web |last=DeVille |first=Chris |title=The Top 40 Pop Songs Of 2019 |url=https://www.stereogum.com/2067368/the-top-40-pop-songs-of-2019/franchises/2019-in-review/ |website=[[Stereogum]] |date=12 December 2019 |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''\n|{{center|5}}\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chow |first1=Andrew |last2=Bruner |first2=Raisa |title=The 10 Best Songs of 2019 |url=https://time.com/5736115/best-songs-2019/ |date=28 November 2019|website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |accessdate=8 December 2019}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n== Commercial performance ==\n{{Summarize section|date=April 2020}}\n=== Asia and Oceania ===\nThe single entered the [[Japan Hot 100]] chart at number 90, then later peaked at number 79.<ref name=\"japanesechart\" /> On the [[The Official Lebanese Top 20|Lebanese Top 20]], it entered at number 14, and later peaked at number eight.<ref name=\"auto\" /> \"Don't Start Now\" entered and peaked at number seven on the [[Recording Industry Association of Malaysia|RIM]] chart in Malaysia, and at number six on the [[Recording Industry Association (Singapore)|RIAS]] chart in Singapore.<ref name=\"malaysianchart\" /><ref name=\"singaporechart\" /> The song entered the [[Gaon Digital Chart]] in South Korea at number 152, and later peaked at number 113.<ref name=\"southkoreanchart\" />\n\n\"Don't Start Now\" also experienced commercial success in Oceania. In Australia, it peaked at number two in its sixth week on the chart, her joint-highest charting single in the country alongside \"[[New Rules (song)|New Rules]]\".<ref name=\"australianchart\" /> The song also peaked at number 3 on the [[Recorded Music NZ]] chart in New Zealand, where it was certified platinum for the sale of 30,000 units.<ref name=\"nzchart\" /><ref name=\"NZcertification\" />\n\n=== Europe ===\nIn the United Kingdom, \"Don't Start Now\" entered the [[UK Singles Chart]] at number two, retaining this position for three consecutive weeks. It fell to number four in its fourth week on the chart, where it spent two weeks in this position. The song then rose from number four to three in its sixth week on the chart.<ref name=\"UKsingleschart\" /> \"Don't Start Now\" was [[Record certification|certified platinum]] by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI) for the sale of 600,000 units.<ref name=\"UKcertification\" />\n\nSimilarly, the single was commercially successful throughout the rest of Europe. In Austria, it became Lipa's fourth single to appear inside the top twenty of the [[\u00d63 Austria Top 40]] chart, debuting at number 12 and peaking at number six.<ref name=\"austrianchart\" /> The song entered the [[Ultratop]] chart in the Flanders region of Belgium at number 12, peaking at number two in its fourth week on the chart.<ref name=\"flanderschart\" /> It also entered the Ultratop chart in the Wallonia region of Belgium at number 39, rising to number seven in its seventh week on the chart.<ref name=\"walloniachart\" /> \"Don't Start Now\" entered at number 93 on the [[Croatian Airplay Chart]]. It later peaked at number one and remained atop of the chart for four consecutive weeks.<ref name=\"croatianchart\" /> In the Czech Republic, it peaked at number 10 on the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|Singles Digit\u00e1l Top 100]] chart, and at number six on the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|R\u00e1dio Top 100]] chart.<ref name=\"czechchart\" /><ref name=\"czechdigitalchart\" /> On its ninth week on the [[Hitlisten]] chart in Denmark, the song peaked at number eight.<ref name=\"danishchart\" /> The single debuted and peaked at number six on the ''[[Eesti Ekspress]]'' chart in Estonia.<ref name=\"estonianchart\" /> In Finland, \"Don't Start Now\" entered the [[The Official Finnish Charts]] at number 20, and peaked at number 13 in its fourth week on the chart.<ref name=\"finnishchart\" /> The song peaked at number 25 on the [[SNEP]] chart in France.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/|title=Top Albums|website=SNEP|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref> In Germany, it entered the [[GfK Entertainment charts|GfK Entertainment Charts]] at number 26. It then rose to number 21 a week later and went on to peak at number 10 in its tenth week on the chart.<ref name=\"germanchart\" />\n\n\"Don't Start Now\" entered and peaked at number 11 on the [[IFPI Greece|Greek International Digital]] chart.<ref name=\"greekIDchart\" /> In Hungary, it peaked at number three on the [[Association of Hungarian Record Companies|Single Top 40]] chart, and at number two on the [[Association of Hungarian Record Companies|Stream Top 40]] chart.<ref name=\"hungarysinglechart\" /><ref name=\"hungarystreamchart\" /> The song also became Lipa's fourth number one single in Ireland, after it debuted atop of the [[Irish Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"irishchart\" /> In Iceland, it peaked at number 31 on the [[Tonlist]] chart.<ref name=\"icelandicchart\">{{Cite web|url=https://plotutidindi.is/lagalistinn/|title=T\u00d3NLISTINN \u2013 Vika 46 \u2013 2019; Pl\u00f6tut\u00ed\u00f0indi|access-date=2019-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508143838/https://plotutidindi.is/lagalistinn/|archive-date=2019-05-08|url-status=dead}}</ref> In Italy, the single peaked at number 11 on the [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI Singles]] chart.<ref name=\"italianchart\" /> On the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|LAIPA]] chart in Latvia, \"Don't Start Now\" entered and peaked at number five.<ref name=\"latvianchart\" /> In Lithuania, the song peaked at number two on the [[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]] chart.<ref name=\"lithuanianchart\" /> It entered and peaked at number four on the [[Luxembourg Digital Song Sales]] chart.<ref name=\"luxdigitalchart\" /> In the Netherlands, the single peaked at number four on the [[Dutch Top 40]] chart and at number six on the [[Single Top 100]] chart.<ref name=\"dutch40chart\" /><ref name=\"dutch100chart\" /> The song was the 68th highest selling single of 2019 in the country.<ref name=\"dutchyearendchart\" /> \"Don't Start Now\" peaked at number nine on the [[VG-lista]] chart in Norway.<ref name=\"norwegianchart\" /> On the [[Polish music charts|Polish Airplay Top 100]] chart, the song entered at number 47. It later peaked at number four.<ref name=\"polishchart\" /> The single also entered and peaked at number 15 on the [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Fonogr\u00e1fica Portuguesa|AFP]] chart in Portugal.<ref name=\"portugesechart\" /> In Russia, \"Don't Start Now\" peaked at number seven on the [[Tophit]] airplay chart.<ref name=\"russianairplaychart\" /> On the [[Airplay 100 (Romania)|Airplay 100]] chart in Romania, the song peaked at number eight.<ref name=\"romanianairplaychart\" /> In Slovakia, the single peaked at number three on the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|Singles Digit\u00e1l Top 100]] chart and at number 22 on the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|R\u00e1dio Top 100]] chart.<ref name=\"slovakianchart\" /><ref name=\"slovakiandigitalchart\" /> It also entered the top forty on the [[PROMUSICAE]] charts in Spain, entering and peaking at number 25.<ref name=\"spanishchart\" /> It was later certified gold for the sale of 20,000 units.<ref name=\"spaincertification\" /> In Sweden, \"Don't Start Now\" entered and peaked at number 12 on the [[Sverigetopplistan]] chart.<ref name=\"swedishchart\" /> The song also peaked at number seven on the [[Swiss Hitparade]], and at number 19 on the [[Tophit]] airplay chart in Ukraine.<ref name=\"swisschart\" /><ref name=\"ukrainianairplaychart\" />\n\n=== Americas ===\nIn the United States \"Don't Start Now\" debuted at number 30 and it became Lipa's third top 40 on the [[US Billboard Hot 100|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref name=\"hot100chart\" /> After fluctuating for several weeks, the track reached a new peak of number two in its nineteenth week on the chart on the issue dated 21 March 2020, becoming Lipa's highest peak on the chart. It also became her fifth top ten on the [[Dance/Mix Show Airplay]] chart, after it rose from number 18 to number five in its 30 November 2019 issue. It would eventually reach number one in its 28 December 2019 issue, resulting in her third number one single on this chart.<ref>[https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8544920/good-faith-madeon-debuts-no-1-top-dance-electronic-albums \"Madeon Shows 'Good Faith' at No. 1 on Top Dance/Electronic Albums Chart\"] from ''Billboard'' (27 November 2019)</ref> <ref>[https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-dance-airplay/2019-12-28 Dance/Mix Show Airplay (December 28, 2019)] from ''Billboard'' (26 December 2019)</ref> It also became her eighth number one on ''Billboard''{{'}}s [[Dance Club Songs]] Chart in its 4 January 2020 issue.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/dance-club-play-songs/2020-01-04|title=Dance Club Songs \u2013 January 4, 2020|work=Billboard|date=4 January 2020|accessdate=31 December 2019}}</ref> It remained number one for a second consecutive week on the chart in its 11 January issue. The song also entered the US [[Rolling Stone Top 100|''Rolling Stone'' Top 100]] chart at number 15 and peaked at number 8 in the issue dated 13 February 2020.<ref name=\"rollingstonechart\" /> In Canada, \"Don't Start Now\" entered at number 16 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] chart. It later peaked at number 3.<ref name=\"canadianchart\" /> \n\nIn Argentina, the song entered on the [[Argentina Hot 100]] chart at number 61, and it then rose to number 19.<ref name=\"argentinachart\" /> In Brazil, the song entered the [[Top 100 Brasil]] chart at a low position of 84 and later peaked at 57.<ref name=\"brazilianchart\" /> Despite this, \"Don't Start Now\" performed well in the country and was certified diamond by [[Pro-M\u00fasica Brasil]], for the sale of 160,000 units.<ref name=\"brazilcertification\" /> It also reached the top forty in Colombia, peaking at number 31 on the [[National-Report]] chart.<ref name=\"colombianchart\" /> On the National-Report chart in Ecuador, the single entered at number 32. It rose to number three the following week.<ref name=\"ecuadorchart\" />\n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video premiered on 1 November and was teased by a trailer upon the release of the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-shares-snippet-of-new-track-dont-start-now-album-2559838|title=Dua Lipa shares new disco-tinged single \"Don't Start Now\"|last=Skinner|first=Tom|website=[[NME (magazine)|NME]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=1 November 2019}}</ref> It was directed by [[Nabil Elderkin|Nabil]] and filmed in October 2019 in [[Brooklyn|Brooklyn, New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-is-supposedly-releasing-new-single-dont-start-now-in-november|title=Dua Lipa is supposedly releasing new single \u201cDon\u2019t Start Now\u201d in November|last=Kenneally|first=Cerys|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|date=15 October 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> The video takes place in two different settings: a basement club and a masked ball, this last one with the appearance of models Alexandra Elizabeth Ljadov, Kyla Coleman and [[Yasmin Wijnaldum]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dua Lipa: Don't Start Now|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt11217692/|website=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=1 January 2020}}</ref> The singer is seen passing through both while dancing and singing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/11/01/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-video|title=Watch Dua Lipa's \"Don't Start Now\" video|last=Renshaw|first=David|website=[[The Fader]]|date=1 November 2019|accessdate=1 November 2019}}</ref> A lyric video was uploaded to her official [[YouTube]] channel on 15 November. As of March 2020 the video has amassed over 200 million views.\n\n==Live performances==\nLipa performed \"Don't Start Now\" for the first time on ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'' on 1 November 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/music-guests-confirmed-for-series-26-of-bbc-ones-the-graham-norton-show__27482/|title=Music guests confirmed for Series 26 of BBC One's The Graham Norton Show|last=White|first=Jack|date=28 October 2019|website=[[The Official Charts Company]]|access-date=4 November 2019}}</ref> On 3 November, the singer performed the song at the [[2019 MTV Europe Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-mtv-emas-907545/|title=Watch Dua Lipa perform 'Don't Start Now' at MTV EMAs|last=Zemler|first=Emily|date=4 November 2019|website=Rolling Stone|access-date=4 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/11/04/dua-lipa-colour-block-queen-puts-epic-performance-mtv-emas-11037792/|title=Dua Lipa is a colour block queen as she puts on an epic performance at the MTV EMAs|last=Woodcock|first=Zara|date=4 November 2019|website=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|access-date=4 November 2019}}</ref> On 10 November, Lipa performed the single on singing competition show ''[[The Voice of Germany]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fanpop.com/clubs/dua-lipa/videos/43094152/title/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-voice-germany-2019|title=Dua Lipa Video: Dua Lipa - Don't Start Now (The Voice of Germany 2019)|last=Inc|first=Fanpop|website=www.fanpop.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref> On 15 November, Lipa performed the song alongside a full set from her debut album at The Pointe in [[Dubai]], and in [[Mumbai]] as part of the OnePlus Music Festival a day later.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeoutdubai.com/bars-nightlife/423158-review-dua-lipa-live-in-dubai|title=Review: Dua Lipa live in Dubai|last=|first=|date=17 November 2019|website=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out Dubai]]|access-date=8 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/dua-lipa-leaves-fans-spellbound-her-breath-taking-performance-city-view-pics-486426|title=Dua Lipa leaves the fans spellbound with her breath taking performance in the city|last=Mrinal|first=Gujare|date=18 November 2019|website=[[Pinkvilla]]|access-date=8 December 2019}}</ref> Lipa also performed the song at the [[American Music Awards of 2019]] and the [[ARIA Music Awards of 2019]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-dont-start-now-2019-amas-916900/|title=Dua Lipa Brings Dancers, Balloons for 'Don't Start Now' at 2019 AMAs|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|date=24 November 2019|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=8 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popsugar.co.uk/celebrity/dua-lipa-aria-awards-photos-2019-46955550|title=It's safe to say Dua Lipa was 'Hotter Than Hell' on the ARIAs red carpet in Australia|last=Gawne|first=Holley|date=27 November 2019|website=[[PopSugar]]|access-date=8 December 2019}}</ref> On 28 November, Lipa performed the song on the Australian morning television show ''[[Sunrise (Australian TV program)|Sunrise]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://7news.com.au/sunrise/entertainment/dua-lipa-headlines-the-sunrise-summer-party-live-from-hamilton-island-c-581275|title=Dua Lipa headlines the Sunrise Summer Party live from Hamilton Island|last=|first=|date=29 November 2019|website=[[Seven News]]|access-date=8 December 2019}}</ref> On 4 December, Lipa performed the single at the [[2019 Mnet Asian Music Awards]] in Japan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ohnotheydidnt.livejournal.com/116606548.html|title=Dua Lipa performs 'Don't Start Now' at MAMA 2019, Nagoya Dome|website=ohnotheydidnt.livejournal.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref> On 17 December, Lipa performed the song on the finale of ''[[The Voice (American season 17)|The Voice]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thatgrapejuice.net/2019/12/dua-lipa-dances-storm-during-dont-start-now-performance-the-voice/|title=Dua Lipa Dances Up A Storm During 'Don't Start Now' Performance On 'The Voice' - That Grape Juice|website=thatgrapejuice.net|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dua Lipa Performs \"Don't Start Now\" - The Voice Live Finale, Part 2 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sMtEfEepLTM|via=[[YouTube]]|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> and on 19 December she performed the single on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/watch-dua-lipa-perform-dont-start-now-on-fallon/|title=Watch Dua Lipa Perform \"Don't Start Now\" on Fallon|website=Pitchfork|access-date=2019-12-23}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Dua Lipa: Don't Start Now|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JlkPChcoHOg|language=en|access-date=2019-12-23}}</ref> The next day the song was performed on the American morning television show ''[[Good Morning America]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/popheads/comments/edoazf/dua_lipa_performs_dont_start_now_live_on_good/|title=r/popheads - Dua Lipa performs Don't Start Now live on Good Morning America|website=reddit|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref> Furthermore, Lipa performed the song on [[Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve]] 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/01/video-dua-lipa-dick-clark-nye/|title=Dua Lipa performs \"Don't Start Now\" on Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve: Watch|date=1 January 2020|website=Consequence of Sound|accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref> On 9 January, Lipa performed the song on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8547667/dua-lipa-performs-dont-start-now-ellen-video|title=Watch Dua Lipa's Fierce Performance of 'Don't Start Now' on 'Ellen'|website=www.billboard.com|date=9 January 2020|language=en|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> On 7 February, Lipa performed the song at the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2020|Sanremo Music Festival]] in Italy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailynewsgh.com/2020/02/07/dua-lipa-performs-dont-start-now-at-sanremo-music-festival-2020/|title=Dua Lipa Performs 'Don't Start Now' at SanRemo Music Festival 2020 {{!}} Daily News|last=Gringo|first=Alhaji|date=2020-02-07|website={{!}} Daily News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> On 30 March 2020, Lipa performed \"Don't Start Now\" by video conference call from her London apartment for ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-dua-lipa-and-her-band-give-video-conference-performance-on-james-cordens-homefest-2638167\"|title=Watch Dua Lipa and her band give video conference performance on James Corden's 'HomeFest'|last=Daly|first=Rhian|website=NME|date=31 March 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref>{{cite web |title=Don't Start Now by Dua Lipa on Apple Music |url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/dont-start-now/1484636581?i=1484636829 |website=[[Apple Music]] |accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n| title1 = Don't Start Now\n| length1 = 3:03\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download \u2013 Dom Dolla Remix<ref name = \"dom dolla\">{{cite web |title=Don't Start Now (Dom Dolla Remix) by Dua Lipa on Apple Music |url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/dont-start-now-dom-dolla-remix/1488350146?i=1488350147 |websit